## Banque de prompts vidéo

5 mouvements vidéo typiques pour les vidéos de restaurants, chefs et plats gastronomiques.

### Mouvement 01 — Reveal d'un ingrédient

```text
Duration: 3s
Use first-frame.png as start frame, last-frame.png as end frame.

Camera: very slow push in.
Motion: tiny droplets and texture become more visible as the camera approaches the ingredient. No artificial movement.
Lighting: soft directional light remains consistent.
Style: cinematic, 24fps, film grain, color graded.
```

### Mouvement 02 — Geste du chef

```text
Duration: 4s
Use first-frame.png as start frame, last-frame.png as end frame.

Camera: static close-up.
Motion: chef hands perform one precise culinary gesture, such as slicing, seasoning, stirring or placing garnish. The movement is controlled, elegant and realistic.
Lighting: warm kitchen light, consistent throughout.
Style: cinematic, 24fps, film grain, color graded.
```

### Mouvement 03 — Cuisson et vapeur

```text
Duration: 4s
Use first-frame.png as start frame, last-frame.png as end frame.

Camera: slight handheld micro-movement, professional documentary feel.
Motion: steam rises naturally from the pan or plate, surface of the food glistens, flame or heat creates subtle movement in the background.
Lighting: warm fire light with soft highlights.
Style: cinematic, 24fps, film grain, color graded.
```

### Mouvement 04 — Dressage final

```text
Duration: 5s
Use first-frame.png as start frame, last-frame.png as end frame.

Camera: slow overhead-to-45-degree tilt.
Motion: chef hand places the final garnish or sauce element on the plate, then exits the frame, leaving the final dish perfectly composed.
Lighting: warm overhead restaurant light, consistent.
Style: cinematic, 24fps, film grain, color graded.
```

### Mouvement 05 — Service à table

```text
Duration: 5s
Use first-frame.png as start frame, last-frame.png as end frame.

Camera: slow tracking shot from the side of the table.
Motion: server places the dish gently in front of the guest, glassware catches warm highlights, background guests remain soft silhouettes.
Lighting: warm candlelight and soft restaurant ambience.
Style: cinematic, 24fps, film grain, color graded.
```

